summaries.short: Alex is tasked to deliver a message to Walter; Zeke and Glenn await their drone inquiry.
summaries.full: Alex is tasked by Zaman's half-brother Raja to get a message to Walter--a mission which Alex hopes will save him from being sent to Baghdad. Walter is greeted with personal and professional surprises at home before taking off for New Delhi. On the aircraft carrier, Zeke and Glenn await their inquiry into the downed drone.

summaries.short: Walter pushes on despite his medical condition; Zeke contemplates a double life; Alex tries to get to Raja.
summaries.full: In New Delhi, Walter defies doctor's orders and meets with the Indian Foreign Minister to urge him to withdraw his troops. Zeke contemplates the merits and perils of leading a double life before he and Glenn take off on a recon mission. In Islamabad, Alex encounters resistance as he tries to deliver a package to Raja.

summaries.short: Walter argues for restraint against Zaman; Alex is interrogated in Islamabad; Zeke and Glenn try to sober up during a critical mission.
summaries.full: With President Navarro and Defense Secretary Grey ordering a military response to General Zaman's threats, Walter argues that an air strike could unleash a world war. Meanwhile, after learning that classified information has been sent from Rafiq's house, Zaman's men storm the place and end up dragging Alex to an undisclosed location for interrogation.

summaries.short: Zeke and Glenn are stranded; Alex and Rafiq search for Fareeda; Walter drops in on the Israeli Foreign Minister.
summaries.full: Zeke and Glenn narrowly escape from two armed men in the tribal region before being picked up by an eccentric British couple. With Fareeda missing, Alex and Rafiq head to her school and encounter a group of girls with nowhere to go. Against the President's orders, Walter pays an unscheduled visit to the Israeli Foreign Minister.

summaries.short: Series Premiere. When a coup erupts in Pakistan, three Americans find themselves entwined in an emerging geopolitical crisis.
summaries.full: Series Premiere. When a coup erupts in Pakistan, three Americans--U.S. Secretary of State Walter Larson (Tim Robbins), Alex Talbott, a lowly Foreign Service officer in Islamabad (Jack Black), and ace Navy fighter pilot & prescription drug dealer Zeke 'Z-Pak' Tilson (Pablo Schreiber)--find themselves entwined in an emerging geopolitical crisis.

summaries.short: Walter runs into Joanne in Tel Aviv; Zeke and Glenn are held hostage; Kittredge shares a revelatory dream with Alex.
summaries.full: Ordered to return to DC, Walter runs into Joanne in Tel Aviv, and angles to use her new position to his advantage. Held hostage by Martin and Vanessa, Zeke and Glenn agree to participate in role-playing games in hopes of a release. Later, Alex meets with Kittredge, who shares a revelatory dream.
